    slug: "the-sciences-of-the-quran-for-children",
    description: `The Sciences of the Quran for Children is an English-language Islamic educational book specifically designed to introduce young Muslim readers to the foundational disciplines of Quranic studies in a manner that is engaging, age-appropriate, and spiritually enriching. The book recognizes that children are naturally curious about the Quran and often ask questions that require knowledge of the Quranic sciences to answer properly, such as how the Quran was revealed, why it was revealed in Arabic, how it was preserved, what tafsir means, and how the verses of the Quran are organized. This book provides clear and satisfying answers to these questions while instilling in children a deep love and respect for the Quran as the word of Allah.

The book is organized into chapters that each cover one of the major sciences of the Quran, presented in language and with examples that children can understand and relate to. The opening chapter introduces the concept of the Quran as Allah's final revelation to humanity, explaining in simple terms how the Quran was sent down to Prophet Muhammad (peace be upon him) through the angel Jibreel over a period of twenty-three years. Subsequent chapters cover the science of revelation (nuzul), explaining the difference between Makkan and Madinan revelations and the reasons why certain verses were revealed in response to specific events; the science of Quranic preservation, describing how the companions memorized and wrote down the Quran and how it was compiled into a single volume during the caliphate of Abu Bakr and Uthman (may Allah be pleased with them); the science of tafsir, introducing the concept of Quranic interpretation and the major scholars who contributed to this field; and the science of tajweed, explaining the rules of Quranic recitation.

Additional chapters introduce children to the concept of asbab al-nuzul (the occasions of revelation), helping them understand that many Quranic verses were revealed in response to real-life situations and questions from the companions. The book also covers the miraculous nature of the Quran (ijaz), the concept of abrogation (naskh) in age-appropriate terms, the names and attributes of the Quran, and the etiquette of handling and reciting the Quran. Throughout the book, colorful illustrations, stories from the lives of the companions, practical examples, and review questions help to reinforce the material and keep young readers engaged. The book includes a glossary of key terms in Arabic and English, making it a useful reference for both children and the parents and teachers who guide their Quranic education. This book is highly recommended for children aged eight to fourteen, for Islamic school curricula, and for family reading time.`,
    metaDescription: "The Sciences of the Quran for Children introduces tafsir, tajweed, preservation, and revelation of the Quran with engaging illustrations."
